Let $numberset$ be a set of three, not necessarily distinct, positive integers.
Show that one can transform $numberset$ into a set containing 0 by a finite
number of applications of the following rule: Select two of the three
integers, say $varxvalue$ and $varyvalue$, where $varxvalue \leq varyvalue$ and replace them with $2varxvalue$ and $varyvalue-varxvalue$.

\end{itemize}
